snippet: Killing terrorist leaders may be a victory for drone strikes, but it has not helped the Obama administration and its Western allies stem the chaos in Yemen and Libya.
abstract: News Analysis; United States has been successful in killing terrorist leaders, but continued chaos in Yemen and Libya underscores limitations of Obama administration and its Western allies.

byline.original: By MARK MAZZETTI and SCOTT SHANE
byline.contributor: Kareem Fahim contributed reporting from Baghdad.

lead_paragraph: Killing terrorist leaders may be a victory for drone strikes, but it has not helped the Obama administration and its Western allies stem the chaos in Yemen and Libya.

headline.main: For U.S., Killing Terrorists Is a Means to an Elusive End
